 set up a standard; publish, and conceal not: say, Babylon is taken, Bel is confounded, Merodach is broken in pieces; her idols are confounded, her images are broken in pieces.","year":-595},{"id":"recx9w4FVuN3JXXRy","ref":"Jer.50.3","text":"For out of the north there cometh up a nation against her, which shall make her land desolate, and none shall dwell therein: they shall remove, they shall depart, both man and beast.","year":-595},{"id":"recWwhQ4pwoKTTER3","ref":"Jer.50.4","text":"In those days, and in that time, saith the LORD, the children of Israel shall come, they and the children of Judah together, going and weeping: they shall go, and seek the LORD their God.","year":-595},{"id":"recs4AO702mxjDBdj","ref":"Jer.50.5","text":"They shall ask the way to Zion with their faces thitherward, saying, Come, and let us join ourselves to the LORD in a perpetual covenant that shall not be forgotten.","year":-595},{"id":"recfeBIusnvKKwkHU","ref":"Jer.50.6","text":"My people hath been lost sheep: their shepherds have caused them to go astray, they have turned them away on the mountains: they have gone from mountain to hill, they have forgotten their restingplace.","year":-595},{"id":"recuua5EXzGjLkyPs","ref":"Jer.50.7","text":"All that found them have devoured them: and their adversaries said, We offend not, because they have sinned against the LORD, the habitation of justice, even the LORD, the hope of their fathers.","year":-595},{"id":"recpS7FKBs3VljlYK","ref":"Jer.50.8","text":"Remove out of the midst of Babylon, and go forth out of the land of the Chaldeans, and be as the he goats before the flocks.","year":-595}]}
